text: The Wag Islands are an uninhabited Canadian arctic islands group in Kivalliq Region, Nunavut, Canada. They are irregularly shaped and are located at the mouth of Chesterfield Inlet. The Inuit hamlet of Chesterfield Inlet is located to the south. ==References== Category:Islands of Chesterfield Inlet Category:Uninhabited islands of Kivalliq Region Category:Islands of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago
